VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'let\'s break down the workflow settings. This top box right here is where you dial in the metadata and define the overall mood of the track. This basically primes the model, dictating how the song should feel'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'before a single lyric is even sung. Down in the bottom box is your actual script. See how we\'re using structural tags like intro, verse one, and chorus. That part is absolutely crucial. The AI relies on those tags to map out the'

[05:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'song\'s progression, making sure the chorus hits with way more infectious energy than the verses. Moving on, we have the BPM, or beats per minute. This acts as the engine of your track, driving the exact speed and overall'

[06:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'energy level. Next up is the time signature. This groups your beats into measures to keep the AI\'s internal rhythm perfectly locked in, like sticking to a standard 4/4 time for a catchy pop beat. The language option is'

[06:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'super straightforward. It just tells the vocal synthesis engine exactly which language to use for your custom lyrics. With the key scale setting, you lay down the harmonic foundation of the track. Your CFG scale controls how strictly the'

[06:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI adheres to your text prompts. You can crank it up to force the model to listen very closely to your tags, or dial it back to give it some breathing room to improvise. Temperature acts as your master'

[06:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'creativity dial. Keeping it low gives you safe, highly predictable melodies, but pushing it higher lets the AI get a bit wild, experimental, and pleasantly unpredictable. Then we have top P, top K, and min P, which all work together as'

[06:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an automatic quality control filter under the hood. These settings dynamically trim away the least likely or mathematically bad musical notes during generation, ensuring your final output sounds incredibly sharp and'

[07:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'professional, rather than chaotic. Right here is where you can easily set the overall length of your song. And finally, we get to the sampler. We\'re using A steps, and the CFG is set to one since we\'re dealing with a Turbo'

[07:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
